    <note>Huang(2) Yong(3) [15994] Was a member of a group of six university students (later known as the six junzi), who memorialized an attack on Ding(1) Daquan [15990]. They included Chen(1) Yizhong [15991] (q.v.), Liu(2) Fu (not in dataset), Lin(1) Zezu [15995], Zeng(1) Wei (not in dataset) and Chen(1) Zong (not in dataset). All were expelled and exiled, but in 1260, the minister of state, Wu(3) Qian(2) [16041], petitioned that they be permitted to go directly to the palace exams and all six earned the jinshi degree in 1262. Fujian TZ, 150.31a. CBD, 4, 2879.From Hartwell's ACTIVITY table:1275:  Apt. Tongqian Shumi yuan shi (State Council).1276:  Promoted to Canzhi zhengshi.</note>
